1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,600
This is a front-opening suitcase that's become really popular in China in recent years. Right up front, there's a padded compartment that protects your laptop.

2
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:14,400
On the back, a mesh pocket holds your power bank and documents, so you can reach them easily without opening the whole case.

3
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:17,700
You don't have to lay it flat on the floor like a clamshell case that opens down the middle.

4
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,700
The back also has a cup holder, so you can set your drink down and keep both hands free while you travel.

5
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:27,200
It has a 66-watt fast-charging port too, so you can charge your phone anytime, anywhere.

6
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:34,000
On the handle, there's a hook for your umbrella or bag, and you can even rest your phone on it.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:50,500
The main section is one deep compartment with plenty of room. You can pack bulky clothes, shoes, and your toiletry bag inside, almost like a small car trunk. It holds enough for a three-to-five-day trip, and it fits large, irregularly shaped items as well.

8
00:00:50,500 --> 00:01:00,700
The wheels at the back are made entirely of TPE, with shock-absorbing springs inside, so they roll smoothly and quietly. You can barely hear them.
